#. type: Content of: <guide><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Baselayout and OpenRC Migration Guide"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This guide shows you how to migrate from baselayout-1 to baselayout-2 and\n"
"OpenRC.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "What's baselayout?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Baselayout provides a basic set of files that are necessary for all systems to\n"
"function properly, such as <path>/etc/hosts</path>. It also provides the basic\n"
"filesystem layout used by Gentoo (i.e. <path>/etc</path>, <path>/var</path>,\n"
"<path>/usr</path>, <path>/home</path> directories).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "What's OpenRC?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"OpenRC is a dependency-based rc system that works with whatever init is provided\n"
"by the system, normally <path>/sbin/init</path>. However, it is <e>not</e> a\n"
"replacement for <path>/sbin/init</path>. The default init used by Gentoo Linux\n"
"is <c>sys-apps/sysvinit</c>, while Gentoo/FreeBSD uses the FreeBSD init provided\n"
"by <c>sys-freebsd/freebsd-sbin</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "So why migrate?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:70
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Originally Gentoo's rc system was built into baselayout 1 and written entirely\n"
"in bash. This led to several limitations. For example, certain system calls need\n"
"to be accessed during boot and this required C-based callouts to be added. These\n"
"callouts were each statically linked, causing the rc system to bloat over time.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:77
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Additionally, as Gentoo expanded to other platforms like\n"
"Gentoo/FreeBSD and Gentoo Embedded, it became impossible to require a bash-based\n"
"rc system. This led to a development of baselayout 2, which is written in\n"
"C and only requires a POSIX-compliant shell. During the development of\n"
"baselayout 2, it was determined that it was a better fit if baselayout merely\n"
"provided the base files and filesystem layout for Gentoo and the rc system\n"
"was broken off into its own package. Thus we have OpenRC.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:87
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"OpenRC was initially developed by <uri link=\"http://roy.marples.name/openrc\">Roy\n"
"Marples</uri> until 2010, and is now maintained by the <uri\n"
"link=\"/proj/en/base/openrc/\">Gentoo OpenRC Project</uri>. OpenRC supports all\n"
"current Gentoo variations (i.e. Gentoo Linux, Gentoo/FreeBSD, Gentoo Embedded,\n"
"and Gentoo Vserver) and other platforms such as FreeBSD and NetBSD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migration to OpenRC"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Migration to OpenRC is fairly straightforward; it will be pulled in as part of\n"
"your regular upgrade process by your package manager. The most important step\n"
"actually comes after you install the new <c>>=sys-apps/baselayout-2</c> and\n"
"<c>sys-apps/openrc</c> packages. It is <e>critical</e> that you run\n"
"<c>dispatch-conf</c> and ensure your <path>/etc</path> is up to date before\n"
"rebooting. "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p><brite>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "Failure to do so will result in an unbootable system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"and will require the use of the Gentoo LiveCD to perform the steps below to\n"
"repair your system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once you've finished updating your config files, there are a few things to\n"
"verify prior to rebooting.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/conf.d/rc"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:125
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<path>/etc/conf.d/rc</path> has been deprecated and any settings you have in\n"
"there will need to be migrated to the appropriate settings in\n"
"<path>/etc/rc.conf</path>. Please read through <path>/etc/rc.conf</path> and\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/rc</path> and migrate the settings. Once you are complete,\n"
"delete <path>/etc/conf.d/rc</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Normally, when you want certain kernel modules automatically loaded at boot, you\n"
"place them into <path>/etc/modules.autoload.d/kernel-2.6</path> along with any\n"
"parameters you wanted to pass to them. In baselayout-2, this file is not used\n"
"anymore. Instead, autoloaded modules and module parameters are placed in one\n"
"file, <path>/etc/conf.d/modules</path>, no matter the kernel version.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:147
#, no-wrap
msgid "An example old style configuration would be:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:150
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/modules.autoload.d/kernel-2.6"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:151
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ivtv\n"
"cx88_dvb video_br=2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "Converting the above example would result in the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:159
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/conf.d/modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:160
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment># Modules autoloaded at boot</comment>\n"
"modules_2_6=\"ivtv cx88_dvb\"\n"
"<comment># Module parameters</comment>\n"
"module_cx88_dvb_args_2_6=\"video_br=2\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:167
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the above examples, the modules and their parameters would only be passed\n"
"to 2.6.x series kernels. The new configuration allows for fine grained\n"
"control over the modules and parameters based on kernel version.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:173
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <b>module*</b> variables are not cumulative. The more version-specific\n"
"variables will override the more general variables.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:178
#, no-wrap
msgid "Please note the difference between <b>module_</b> and <b>modules_</b>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid "An in-depth example would be:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "detailed example of /etc/conf.d/modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:186
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment># Only load ivtv for 2.6.23-gentoo-r5</comment>\n"
"modules_2_6_23_gentoo_r5=\"ivtv\"\n"
"<comment># Only load cx88_dvb for 2.6.23 kernels (other than -gentoo-r5)</comment>\n"
"modules_2_6_23=\"cx88_dvb\"\n"
"<comment># Only load tun and usbserial for 2.6.x series kernels where x != 23</comment>\n"
"modules_2_6=\"tun usbserial\"\n"
"<comment># Otherwise load ochi1394 and ieee1394</comment>\n"
"modules=\"ohci1394 ieee1394\"\n"
"\n"
"<comment># For 2.6.23-gentoo-r5, pass video_br=2 to cx88_dvb</comment>\n"
"module_cx88_dvb_args_2_6_23_gentoo_r5=\"video_br=2\"\n"
"<comment># For 2.6.x series kernels, always pass vendor and product</comment>\n"
"module_usbserial_args_2_6=\"vendor=0x1410 product=0x2110\"\n"
"<comment># Always pass debug to ieee1394</comment>\n"
"module_ieee1394_args=\"debug\" \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:206
#, no-wrap
msgid "Boot runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:210
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>boot</c> runlevel performs several important steps for every machine. For\n"
"example, making sure your root filesystem is mounted read/write, that your\n"
"filesystems are checked for errors, that your mountpoints are available, and\n"
"that the <path>/proc</path> pseudo-filesystem is started at boot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:217
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"With OpenRC, volume management services for your block storage devices are no\n"
"longer run automatically at boot. This includes lvm, raid, swap, device-mapper\n"
"(dm), dm-crypt, and the like. You must ensure the appropriate initscript\n"
"for these services is in the <c>boot</c> runlevel, otherwise it's possible that\n"
"your system will not boot!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:225
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"While the OpenRC ebuild will attempt to do this migration for you, you should\n"
"verify that it migrated all the volume management services properly:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "Display all services in boot runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>ls -l /etc/runlevels/boot/</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:234
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you don't see root, procfs, mtab, swap, and fsck in the above listing,\n"
"perform the following to add them to the <c>boot</c> runlevel:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding critical services to the boot runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>rc-update add root boot</i>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add procfs boot</i>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add mtab boot</i>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add fsck boot</i>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add swap boot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you know you use mdraid and lvm but do not see them above, you would run\n"
"the following to add initscripts to the <c>boot</c> runlevel:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding mdraid and lvm to the boot runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>rc-update add mdraid boot</i>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add lvm boot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:259
#, no-wrap
msgid "Udev"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:263
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"OpenRC no longer starts <c>udev</c> by default, but it does need to be present\n"
"in the <c>sysinit</c> runlevel to be started. The OpenRC ebuild should detect if\n"
"<c>udev</c> was previously enabled and add it to the <c>sysinit</c> runlevel.\n"
"However, to be safe, check if <c>udev</c> is present:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:269
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verifying udev"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ls -l /etc/runlevels/sysinit</i>\n"
"lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 14 2009-01-29 08:00 /etc/runlevels/sysinit/udev -> \\\n"
"/etc/init.d/udev\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:276
#, no-wrap
msgid "If <c>udev</c> is not listed, add it to the correct runlevel:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:279
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding udev to the sysinit runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:280
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>rc-update add udev sysinit</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:286
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:290
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Due to baselayout and OpenRC being broken into two different packages, your\n"
"net.eth0 initscript may disappear during the upgrade process. To replace this\n"
"initscript and re-add it to the default runlevel, please perform the\n"
"following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:296
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding back missing net.eth0 script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:297
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd /etc/init.d</i>\n"
"# <i>ln -s net.lo net.eth0</i>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add net.eth0 default</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:303
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are missing any other network initscripts, follow the instructions above\n"
"to re-add them. Simply replace <c>eth0</c> with the name of your network\n"
"device.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Also, <path>/etc/conf.d/net</path> (oldnet) no longer uses bash-style arrays\n"
"for configuration. Please review\n"
"<path>/usr/share/doc/openrc-&lt;version&gt;/net.example</path> for configuration\n"
"instructions. Conversion should be relatively straight-forward, converting to\n"
"newlines for seperate entries, for example a static IP assignment would change\n"
"as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "Old /etc/conf.d/net style"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config_eth0=( \"192.168.1.37 netmask 255.255.255.0 brd 192.168.1.255\" )\n"
"routes_eth0=( \"default via 192.168.1.100\" \"10.0.0.0/8 via 192.168.1.2\" )\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:322
#, no-wrap
msgid "New /etc/conf.d/net style"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"config_eth0=\"192.168.1.37 netmask 255.255.255.0 brd 192.168.1.255\"\n"
"routes_eth0=\"default via 192.168.1.100\n"
"10.0.0.0/8 via 192.168.1.2\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid "Clock"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:335
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Clock settings have been renamed from <path>/etc/conf.d/clock</path> to your\n"
"system's native tool for adjusting the clock. This means on Linux it will be\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/hwclock</path> and on FreeBSD it will be\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/adjkerntz</path>. Systems without a working real time clock\n"
"(RTC) chip should use <path>/etc/init.d/swclock</path>, which sets the system\n"
"time based on the mtime of a file which is created at system shutdown. The\n"
"initscripts in <path>/etc/init.d/</path> have also been renamed accordingly, so\n"
"make sure the appropriate script for your system has been added to the boot\n"
"runlevel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:347
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Additionally, the <c>TIMEZONE</c> variable is no longer in this file. Its\n"
"contents are instead found in the <path>/etc/timezone</path> file. If it\n"
"doesn't exist, you will of course have to create it with your timezone. Please\n"
"review both of these files to ensure their correctness.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The proper value for this file is the path relative to your timezone from\n"
"<path>/usr/share/zoneinfo</path>. For example, for someone living on the east\n"
"coast of the United States, the following would be a correct setting:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/timezone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:360
#, no-wrap
msgid "America/New_York\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:366
#, no-wrap
msgid "XSESSION"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:370
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The XSESSION variable is no longer found in <path>/etc/rc.conf</path>. Instead,\n"
"you can set the XSESSION variable per-user in <path>~/.bashrc</path> (or\n"
"equivalent), or system-wide in <path>/etc/env.d/</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:376
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here's an example of setting XSESSION for the whole system:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting XSESSION system-wide"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>echo 'XSESSION=\"Xfce4\"' > /etc/env.d/90xsession</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:384 en/openrc-migration.xml:404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You must run <c>env-update</c> after creating a file in <path>/etc/env.d</path>,\n"
"and then logout and login for it to take effect. If you set the variable in\n"
"<path>~/.bashrc</path>, you can re-source the file with <c>source\n"
"~/.bashrc</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:393
#, no-wrap
msgid "EDITOR and PAGER"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:397
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The EDITOR variable is no longer found in <path>/etc/rc.conf</path>.  Both\n"
"EDITOR and PAGER are set by default in <path>/etc/profile</path>.  You should\n"
"change this as needed in your <path>~/.bashrc</path> (or equivalent) file or\n"
"create <path>/etc/env.d/99editor</path> and set the system default there.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:413
#, no-wrap
msgid "Boot log"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:417
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Previously, you could log the boot process by using\n"
"<c>app-admin/showconsole</c>. However, OpenRC now handles all logging\n"
"internally, so there's no need for the hacks that <c>showconsole</c> employed.\n"
"You can safely unmerge <c>showconsole</c>. To continue logging boot messages,\n"
"just set the appropriate variable in <path>/etc/rc.conf</path>. Logs will appear\n"
"in <path>/var/log/rc.log</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:425
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling boot logging in /etc/rc.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:426
#, no-wrap
msgid "rc_logger=\"YES\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:432
#, no-wrap
msgid "local.start and local.stop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:436
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"With OpenRC, <path>/etc/conf.d/local.start</path> and <path>local.stop</path>\n"
"are deprecated. During the migration to OpenRC, the files are moved to\n"
"<path>/etc/local.d</path> and gain the suffix <path>.start</path> or\n"
"<path>.stop</path>. OpenRC then executes those in alphabetic order.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:445
#, no-wrap
msgid "System sub-types: Virtualization special cases"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:449
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the early versions of OpenRC, we explictly detected multiple types of\n"
"virtualization, and used that detection to note when certain init scripts\n"
"should be skipped, using the <b>keyword</b> call in the <b>depend</b>\n"
"functions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:456
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, as of the 0.7.0 release, you are required to explicitly configure the\n"
"sub-type using the <b>rc_sys</b> variable in <path>/etc/rc.conf</path>. The\n"
"sub-type should be set to match the virtualization environment that the given\n"
"root is in. In general, the non-empty <b>rc_sys</b> value should be within the\n"
"virtual containers; The host node will have <b>rc_sys=\"\"</b>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:464
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you do not have any specific sub-type, please use the default of an empty\n"
"string <b>\"\"</b>. If the variable is unset, you will be given a warning and we\n"
"will attempt to use the old detection algorithm.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:470
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you do not know what value your system was using with the automatic\n"
"detection, you should temporarily comment out the <b>rc_sys</b> variable and\n"
"run the detection command, <c>rc -S</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

