#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:568
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changed functionality"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:570
#, no-wrap
msgid "The pause action"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:574
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Previously it was possible to temporarily stop a service without taking down all\n"
"the depending services by using <c>/etc/init.d/service pause</c>. In OpenRC, the\n"
"<c>pause</c> action was removed; this functionality is supported by the\n"
"<c>/etc/init.d/service --nodeps stop</c>, which also works in the old\n"
"baselayout.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:584
#, no-wrap
msgid "rootfs entry in /etc/mtab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/openrc-migration.xml:588
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Previously, the initial <b>rootfs</b> entry was removed from\n"
"<path>/etc/mtab</path>, and only the real root <path>/</path> entry was\n"
"present. The duplicate rootfs item was actually added back during shutdown.\n"
"In OpenRC, both entries must be present for full support of initramfs and\n"
"tmpfs-on-root. This also means that less writing is required during shutdown.\n"
msgstr ""
